", "text/vnd.vegguide.org-wikitext": "See http://www.bayareaveg.org for more information about vegetarian dining in the Bay Area."}, "last_modified_datetime": "2009-01-27T05:45:49Z", "user": {"website": "http://www.exploreveg.org", "name": "conde.kedar", "veg_level": "4", "veg_level_description": "vegan", "uri": "http://www.vegguide.org/user/4795", "bio": {"text/html": "

I was born and raised in Illinois and lived in beautiful Minnesota from 2007 to 2010. I've been vegan since 2004 and I've lived and traveled all over the world, from Alaska to Brazil to India and Cambodia.

I was formerly a board member and volunteer for Compassionate Action for Animals in Minneapolis.

I have no set scoring system for rating restaurants, though unique or unusual dishes/ingredients will draw my attention, and edgy or creative foods will win my admiration. If you've got that undefinable "x" factor, you'll get 5 stars from me; that said, few places have received 5 stars in my book.

Some miscellaneous odds and ends:

Favorite books: All the Names by Jose Saramago; Siddhartha by Herman Hesse; The Old Man and the Sea by Ernest Hemingway; and As I Lay Dying by William Faulkner.

Favorite movies: The Straight Story; The Fog of War; Kundun; Bringing Out the Dead; The Thin Red Line; Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid; Rashomon; The Seventh Seal; Amores Perros; The Lives of Others; Wall-E

Favorite tv shows: The Wire; Battlestar Galactica; Deadwood; Freaks and Geeks; The X-Files; Arrested Development; Breaking Bad; Mad Men; The Simpsons; Futurama
